params.amount0Desired: Max amount of token0 to deposit
params.amount1Desired: Max amount of token1 to deposit
params.to: address that plp should be transfered

returns._0: The address of the Uniswap V3 Pool

rebalance().details: Swaps imbalanced token. Finds base position and limit position for imbalanced token if we don't have balance during swap because of price impact. mints all amounts to this position(including earned fees)

rerange().details: Finds base position and limit position for imbalanced token mints all amounts to this position(including earned fees)

tickSpacing().details: Ticks can only be used at multiples of this value, minimum of 1 and always positive e.g.: a tickSpacing of 3 means ticks can be initialized every 3rd tick, i.e., ..., -6, -3, 0, 3, 6, ... This value is an int24 to avoid casting even though it is always positive.

withdraw(uint256,address).details: Removes proportional amount of liquidity from Uniswap.

returns.amount0: Amount of token0 sent to recipient
returns.amount1: Amount of token1 sent to recipient

deposit(uint256,uint256,address).notice: Deposits tokens in proportion to the Optimizer's current ticks.

pool().notice: A Uniswap pool facilitates swapping and automated market making between any two assets that strictly conform to the ERC20 specification

rebalance().notice: Updates Optimizer's positions. Can only be called by the governance.

tickLower().notice: The lower tick of the range

tickUpper().notice: The upper tick of the range

token0().notice: The first of the two tokens of the pool, sorted by address

token1().notice: The second of the two tokens of the pool, sorted by address

withdraw(uint256,address).notice: Withdraws tokens in proportion to the Optimizer's holdings.
